Neural Networks, Probabilistic Methods. 

Neural Networks: The paper mentions that the LBG-U method is inspired by neural networks, specifically the Kohonen self-organizing map. The authors explain how they modified the LBG algorithm to incorporate the self-organizing map concept, resulting in the LBG-U method. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper discusses the use of probability distributions in the LBG-U method, specifically the Gaussian mixture model. The authors explain how the LBG-U method uses the Gaussian mixture model to model the probability distribution of the input data, which is then used to generate the codebook.
